##"At present, it is not clear how strong the spread of Fuyang is. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Tang Qi, the paper

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Member of the Expert Group of the National Health Commission, Jiang Rongmeng, chief physician of the Department of infection, Temple of Earth Hospital, Beijing. Tang Qitu, _ thepaper_news _

On the afternoon of March 5, the Beijing Support Wuhan Medical Team held a long-distance severe case discussion between Beijing and Wuhan in the Wuhan Union Hospital area to exchange experience in the treatment of severe patients and hospital infection.

At present, the Beijing medical team is mainly responsible for the wards on the 8th, 10th and 12th floors of the Wuhan Union Hospital, the paper www.thepaper.cn  learned from the meeting. As of March 3, a total of 300 patients were admitted, 78 patients with severe diseases were admitted, and 68 patients were discharged.

As a member of the Expert Group of the National Health Commission, Jiang Rongmeng, director of the Infection Department of Temple of Earth Hospital in Beijing, came to Wuhan as early as January 9 to guide the prevention and control of the epidemic of NCP. He has persisted for more than 50 days, became one of the longest-serving experts in Wuhan.

As NCP is a self-limited disease, there is no effective antiviral drug. Instead, there are many clinical side effects caused by antiviral drug. Therefore, the first priority should be to do no harm to patients, Jiang said at the meeting, as far as possible to consider the patient's side effects, can be tolerated and other issues.

As for hormone use, Jiang says he and Bian Xiuwu, an academician, learned in a recent discussion of pathology that the new coronavirus, in general, harms the immune system and the lung in two ways, the other organs are basically caused by Secondary Hypoxia. From some medical records, the patient's spleen and lymph nodes "a desolate, barren, " in this case also with hormones, the patient's immune function is unable to restore, hormone use must be careful.

In addition, many critically ill patients died, the Alveoli, macrophages, there are still a large number of new coronavirus. "It also explains the 'reactivation' of the virus in many patients upon discharge from the hospital. We believe that the virus has not been completely eliminated, that the negative result of the throat swab test is only an illusion, and that there is still virus in the lungs, which will bring new challenges to our prevention and control work, " he said.

In an interview with thepaper.cn, Jiang further explained the problem of "Fu Yang" in discharged patients, which is currently of great concern.

He said that some patients with "Fu Yang" in the body of the virus has not been completely cleared, nucleic acid detection sensitivity is limited. "We are now seeing cases where the virus can be positive for more than 30 days or even more than 40 days. If the patient meets the criteria for discharge after the first three weeks of treatment, but in fact he has more than 10 days, 20 days left (possibly with the virus) , so the state in the 6th and 7th edition of the diagnosis and treatment plan requires isolation for another two weeks after discharge, to avoid contact with others, is to prevent the virus has not been completely cleared of the situation."

However, Jiang Rongmeng also admitted that at present, "Fu Yang" how much transmission is unclear, because the positive is not necessarily true virus, there may be virus bodies or fragments, so also continue to study to see whether there is infectious.

Previously, on February 28, Guo Yanhong, an inspector of the Medical Administration and Hospital Authority of the National Health Commission, introduced at a press conference of the joint prevention and control mechanism of the State Council. Some provinces reported that they had cured the discharged patients, during the follow-up visit, positive nucleic acid test was found. Surveillance found that this part of the patients did not happen to infect others, and another part of the patients tested negative for the new coronavirus nucleic acid.

As for whether IGM and IGG tests can be used as a means to determine discharge from the hospital, he told The Paper, antibody tests have nothing to do with discharge from the hospital, antibodies have nothing to do with infectivity, antibody tests are only used as a supplementary diagnosis, a person who develops antibodies is infected with the virus. When the nucleic acid test isn't 100% positive, and he has antibodies, we can make a diagnosis.

This issue is edited by Chang Chen
